<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="82" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Riedl</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-11-21"><hi rend="italic">November 21,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: I have received your note of November
                            18, inclosing brochure in the matter of the claim for indemnity by the
                            Austro-Hungarian Government for the shooting of certain of its subjects
                            at Lattimer, Pa., for which I desire to thank you. The matter will
                            receive my early attention.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>